  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "Study designs are used for which of the following purposes?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Formulating a hypothesis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Testing a hypothesis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Confirming a hypothesis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "All of the above",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. All of the above",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:666px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Formulation of a hypothesis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">A hypothesis is formulated when no knowledge about a new disease exists. Descriptive epidemiology, which focuses on time, place, and person, helps in these cases. For instance, early in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2d364aeaf7169277718529fa58f6ea\">COVID-19</span> outbreak, it was hypothesised as a type of pneumonia.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Testing a hypothesis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">Testing addresses how and why a disease occurs and is a key aspect of Analytical epidemiology. Eg; comparing individuals with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2d364aeaf7169277718529fa58f6ea\">COVID-19</span> to those without it to understand the disease better.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Confirmation of a hypothesis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">The disease is confirmed through Experimental or Interventional epidemiology. Eg; once <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2d364aeaf7169277718529fa58f6ea\">COVID-19</span> was confirmed, vaccines and treatments were developed</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "https://image.prepladder.com/content/czuke9Dp61DoBYiUWDL81726234148.mp3",
      "video": "",
      "uid": "0c30d687"
    },
    {
