    {
      "text": "A research team conducts a study to investigate the association between smoking and bladder cancer. They select a group of patients with and without bladder cancer and compare their smoking history. Which of the following best describes the significance of the study in this scenario?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "It allows for the determination of the incidence of bladder cancer among smokers and non-smokers.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "It helps to establish a temporal relationship between smoking and bladder cancer.",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "It is a cost-effective and efficient way to study the association between smoking and bladder cancer.",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "It can be used to follow patients over time to observe the development of bladder cancer.",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. It is a cost-effective and efficient way to study the association between smoking and bladder cancer.",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Aspect</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Case-Control Study</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Cohort Study</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Compares individuals with a disease (cases) to those without (controls)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Follows a group (cohort) over time to see who develops the disease.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Study Design</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Retrospective or prospective.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Prospective (or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b9b60f7e016927771978a4311da4f\">retrospective</span> in some designs).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Data Collection</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Usually relies on existing records or interviews</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Collects data over time, often with direct measurements.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Population</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Starts with disease status (cases vs. controls)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Starts with exposure status (exposed vs. unexposed).</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Advantages</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>- Quick and inexpensive.</p>\n<p>- Useful for rare diseases.</p>\n<p>- Can study multiple exposures.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>- Can establish <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"637ea4d17516927772003be2b2aae4\">temporal</span> relationships.</p>\n<p>- Useful for studying multiple outcomes.</p>\n<p>- Less bias in exposure measurement</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Disadvantages</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>- <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"607476ab371692777196d0cb2f13bc\">Prone</span> to recall bias.</p>\n<p>- Cannot directly measure incidence.</p>\n<p>- <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88261f221b169277719869abab319a\">Selection bias</span> may occur.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>- Time-consuming and expensive.</p>\n<p>- Requires large sample sizes.</p>\n<p>- Loss to follow-up can affect results.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
